SP.P:
There you totally mistake his character, Lady Bab:—no—he has the heart of an Oldworth. (addressing himself to Mr. Oldworth) Though I confess with very different manners; his expression often puts me in mind of the harsh preparation of instruments;
your ear is jarred, before it is delighted—but at∣tend to his sentiments, and as Hamlet says,
He will discourse most excellent Musick. He never said or did an ill-natured thing in his life.
